caption: Seems like the premiere party place for the younger crowd. It has that Miami dance club vibe to it. There is a dress code to get inside which is enforced strictly. So everybody grab your vodkas and dance the night away to the musical stylings of Pitbull, Jason Derulo, Ne-Yo and many other similar artists. It has an upstairs that I was abruptly denied access to because apparently there was a private party or something. I asked to go upstairs just to look at it for a second and was still denied. You are a great bouncer. You deserve your job. The security here is very strict, tight and enforced or in other words they are not playin'. If you've read this whole review obviously this is a joke but everything is real. It's not a bad place though.

Loved the prime location spot and the EDM DJ!!    It’s nice to see that the Midwest is up to date with music blends that you would normally witness/hear in big cities.   A must place to visit if your looking for a a step above the normal atmosphere.  ❣️

Iowa City is one week away from the University of Iowa beginning its in-person classes during a global pandemic. Social distancing, wearing a mask, and staying in is necessary if the virus is to ever go away. Summit has instead chosen to advertise their cheap drinks, drawing large groups of students to party in a crowded bar. They may say that they socially distance and enforce masks while customers aren’t eating or drinking, but we’ve seen the videos showing otherwise. Summit is playing a part in spreading COVID-19, and putting profit above the well-being of their community.  You won’t have any customers if we’re all dead.
Started my daughter’s 21st off here. The man behind the bar was amazing. In between drinks he would give her water and he always checked in with our group to make sure we were good.

The Hawkeye burger should be on the list of things Iowa students need to try before leaving, absolutely delicious. Fast and friendly service, plenty of TVs, and fill-your-plate fries. Great spot for lunch or for a night out in Iowa City!

The most undergraduate of undergraduate bars.  Seems to have a more Chicago-heavy clientele.  Purports to be a Blackhawks bar, but will turn off the game sound in favor of bad club music at the first inkling of a weekend dance crowd.  When upstairs is open it's an above average venue for dancing, but I have yet to figure out when or why they decide to open this area up.

Extremely disrespectful staff, especially the owner Brad. Brad is a small man on a power trip. He feels the need to belittle women and ended up placing his hands on me. He pushed and shoved me out of the bar when I was already willingly walking out. I was poorly mistreated all because of their mistake of their disorganization behind the bar. I was told they did not have my card when I went to go close my tab. I became frustrated and verbally expressed how upset I was that they lost my card. They proceeded to kick me out, that is when Brad placed his hands on me. The next day I called to double check on my card and what do you know.. They had it the whole time! Instead of just giving my card back when I went to pick it up, Brad continued to humiliate me and raise his voice. Beware if you ever go into summit, as they cannot be trusted. Prime example: Brad.

Dirtiest place I've ever been to. Got there right after the homecoming football game and when you walked in it smelled of vommit. We would of left then but we were meeting friends there. Got served a Miller lite bottle with puke on it. For real....it was puke. Took it back and they apologized and they admitted someone puked all over a bunch of beer. How the bartender didn't notice that before serving says something about their staff. Their bathrooms were the worst I'd ever seen. Who ever had to clean them later ( if they even did) would of had to wear a rubber body suit. They should of just called hazmat to do the job. It was nasty from noon till midnight (unfortunately we had to go back later to see friends before we left town). They did mop their main floor at one time during the early evening time but over looked the bathrooms. I do blame the nasty people who have no respect for public property but that's what happens at bars with young college students, but as bar owners you know this.....I shouldn't have to leave your establishment to pee elsewhere. And people paid $5 to go here?? Save your money and go elsewhere!

A while back I decided to write a review on summit when I was having a very bad day, and it was brought to my attention so I would like to redo this. I said before that the fries were over seasoned, I still believe this, on some days, others they are pretty good. I also said that it is stupid that they charge $1 for a box. I still feel that way. However that is most-likely the owner's choice and shouldn't reflect upon the staff. Which brings me to my last point, the staff I said before was mostly good and friendly. I believe I may have been referring to newer wait staff as the ones who brought down my opinion, however that is unfair, as any newer person wouldn't be as good as the experienced ones. The wait staff is very good, especially those that are able to take multiple orders with only their memory and get it all right. And they all are very friendly.  So I would like to apologize to the staff, as because I was having a bad day, I ended up taking it out in a review. And I thank the gentleman host at summit for bringing it to my attention as an unfair review is unjust.
